	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Aug 9th 8:43 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.82]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Alliance is handier than you'd think if used well.&nbsp;&nbsp;NOT for bumping your faction up one level, that can be done easily enough.  But rather, for getting you from KOS to amiable with an enchanter's help.  Consider some quest you'd like to do but you're KOS  and have to make it to at least amiable.  If an enchanter charms a mob that mob then registers indifferent to those around him.  Add alliance, and voila! you're amiable.  Turn in your quest items, take that desired reward, and tuck this little baby in the bank for the next time it comes up.  Insta overseer hammer for goody twoshoes is just the beginning.  When used with an enchanter, these do very well as a poor man's puppet strings.<br><br>Meredeth, 60th ench, Tunare<br>&nbsp;<br>Meredeth, 60 ench, Tunare</td></tr>
